article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- — Brandon Walker scored 19 points, Robert Ford III had a double=double and Montana State beat Idaho State 77-70 on Monday night. Walker added seven rebounds for the Bobcats (9-10, 4-2 Big Sky Conference). Ford finished with 18 points and 13 rebounds. Chika Nduka shot 6 of 11 from the field to finish with 12 points. Maleek Arington led the way for the Bengals (7-13, 2-5) with 15 points, five assists and two steals. AJ Burgin added 14 points. Kiree Huie had 11 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
